



File 1: Network Security and Monitoring (Italian PA Context).md

Skill: Network Security, Segmentation, and GDPR-Compliant Monitoring

Foundational Knowledge:

    Italian PA Network Architecture: Understanding of the SPC (Sistema Pubblico di Connettività) and migration toward cloud connectivity models.

    ACN Perimetro di Sicurezza Nazionale Cibernetica (PSNC): Identification of which assets (if any) fall under the notification obligation for critical networks.

    GDPR Art. 32 (Security of Processing): Requirement for network segregation to prevent unauthorized access to personal data (e.g., separating Anagrafe Tributaria traffic from guest Wi-Fi).

    Protocols: Deep understanding of protocols used in legacy Italian PA systems (e.g., CIE login flows, SPID authentication traffic over SAML/HTTPS).

Tools and Practical Competencies:

    IDS/IPS for Public Administration: Configuration of Suricata with specific rulesets for Italian threat actors targeting local government.

    Ntopng/nProbe: NetFlow analysis to verify that PagoPA or IO App backend calls originate only from authorized application servers.

    Wireshark/Tcpdump: Detection of unencrypted Codice Fiscale transmission over the wire (strict GDPR violation).

    Key Activities:

        Ensure VLAN segmentation between the "Ufficio Protocollo" (document management network) and "Biblioteca Pubblica" (public internet access).

        Monitor for anomalous RDP connections from external IPs (common entry vector in ransomware attacks on Italian municipalities).

        Log retention policy aligned with Garante Privacy guidelines: Network flow data retention limited strictly to the time necessary for security purposes (max 6-12 months without specific justification).

File 2: Web Application Security (Local Government Services).md

Skill: Securing Municipal Portals, SPID/CIE Authentication, and GDPR Data Subject Rights Portals

Foundational Knowledge:

    Italian Digital Identity Ecosystem: Security analysis of SPID (SAML 2.0) and CIE ID (OIDC) integration endpoints.

    GDPR Art. 25 (Data Protection by Design and by Default): Preventing data leakage via insecure direct object references (IDOR) in online "Pratiche Edilizie" or "Iscrizione Scuola" portals.

    AgID Guidelines: Compliance with Linee Guida AgID for the development of secure software in Public Administration.

    OWASP API Security Top 10: Critical for the PDND (Piattaforma Digitale Nazionale Dati) interoperability APIs.

Tools and Practical Competencies:

    Burp Suite / ZAP: Intercepting and modifying requests to municipal websites (e.g., bypassing filters on Segnalazioni Online forms).

    FFUF / Dirbuster: Discovery of exposed administrative panels (/gestione-istanze, /admin-pa) on subdomains of *.gov.it.

    SSL Labs / Testssl.sh: Verification of TLS configuration on institutional portals (AgID requirement for minimum TLS 1.2, recommended 1.3).

    Key Activities:

        GDPR Specific Test: Verify that the response body to a citizen's login does NOT contain sensitive Codice Fiscale when only the name is requested by the frontend (Data Minimization).

        Access Control Audit: Test if Citizen A can view the IMU payment history of Citizen B by changing an incremental numeric ID in the URL (?id_contribuente=12345).

File 3: Cloud Security (Polo Strategico Nazionale & GDPR).md

Skill: Secure Migration to PSN (Polo Strategico Nazionale) and Qualified Cloud Providers

Foundational Knowledge:

    Qualification Criteria: Understanding of ACN Cloud Qualification (Qualificazione dei servizi cloud per la PA - QI/Q2/Q3).

    Data Sovereignty: Strict adherence to Art. 46 GDPR regarding data transfer outside the EU/EEA; verification that all infrastructure resides within Italian/European data centers.

    GDPR Art. 28 (Data Processing Agreement): Ability to audit the Responsabile del Trattamento (Cloud Provider) contract for security clauses.

    Determina AgID 628/2021: Security requirements for cloud services used by PA.

Tools and Practical Competencies:

    Prowler / ScoutSuite: Cloud Security Posture Management (CSPM) scan against AWS/Azure/Oracle Cloud environments to detect misconfigurations that would violate ACN's Minimum Measures.

    IaC Scanning (Checkov / tfsec): Prevent deployment of S3 Buckets / Blob Containers with public-read ACL containing Backup di Database Tributi.

    Key Activities:

        Encryption Verification: Confirm that all backups containing personal data are encrypted with keys managed in HSM or KMS under the exclusive control of the Public Administration.

        IAM Hygiene: Revoke permanent access keys and enforce Temporary Credentials for administrators managing infrastructure (AgID requirement for privileged account protection).

File 4: Vulnerability Assessment (ACN Minimum Measures & GDPR DPIA).md

Skill: Risk Assessment and Compliance with Italian Minimum ICT Security Measures (Misure Minime ACN)

Foundational Knowledge:

    ACN Minimum Measures: Detailed knowledge of the Misure Minime di Sicurezza ICT per le Pubbliche Amministrazioni (Circolare ACN 1/2019 and subsequent updates).

    GDPR Art. 35 (DPIA): Conducting a Data Protection Impact Assessment (Valutazione d'Impatto) when introducing new security tools or vulnerability scanners that process metadata of employees/citizens.

    NIS 2 Transposition (D.Lgs. 138/2024): Reporting obligations for incidents affecting essential services provided by the municipality.

Tools and Practical Competencies:

    Vulnerability Scanning: Use of Greenbone/OpenVAS or Nessus configured with compliance checks for CIS Benchmarks tailored to Italian PA environments (Windows Server with Carta Nazionale dei Servizi middleware).

    Active Directory Security: Use of PingCastle and BloodHound to identify paths to Domain Admin that could be exploited via Pass-the-Hash (very common in under-staffed municipal IT departments).

    Key Activities:

        ACN Compliance Scan: Verify ABSC 1 (Inventory of Authorized Devices) and ABSC 4 (Dedicated Admin Workstations) implementation status.

        GDPR-Focused Scan: Identify unencrypted database backups stored on NAS/SAN devices accessible via SMB v1.

        Remediation Tracking: Create a Risk Register linked to the annual PIAO (Piano Integrato di Attività e Organizzazione) cybersecurity section.

File 5: Incident Response & GDPR Breach Notification (72h Deadline).md

Skill: Managing Ransomware and Data Breaches in Compliance with Art. 33 GDPR and ACN Reporting

Foundational Knowledge:

    GDPR Art. 33 (Notification Timeline): Absolute requirement to notify the Garante per la Protezione dei Dati Personali within 72 hours of becoming aware of a personal data breach.

    Italian Criminal Code (Art. 615-ter/ter.1): Legal implications of unauthorized access to computer systems and data exfiltration.

    CSIRT Italia: Role of the Italian Computer Security Incident Response Team in coordinating national response.

    PEC (Certified Email): Legal validity and forensic preservation of incident communications sent via PEC.

Tools and Practical Competencies:

    Triage & Containment: Immediate isolation of compromised endpoints using EDR policies (e.g., Microsoft Defender for Endpoint network isolation) to stop lateral movement from the Ufficio Anagrafe to the Ufficio Tributi.

    Forensic Collection: Use of Velociraptor or KAPE to acquire volatile data and registry hives before powering off a server, ensuring chain of custody for potential judicial proceedings.

    Communication Template: Use of the Garante Privacy's specific form for data breach notifications.

    Key Activities:

        Breach Scoping: Determine exactly whose data was exfiltrated (Residents? Employees? Minors?) to trigger specific notification requirements (Art. 34 - Communication to Data Subjects).

        Ransomware Playbook: Executing a specific Playbook for Ransomware in Italian Municipalities, including liaison with Agenzia delle Entrate if tax collection systems are impacted.

File 6: Security Operations & Forensics (GDPR Accountability & Log Management).md

Skill: Centralized Logging, Auditing, and Demonstrating GDPR Compliance (Accountability Principle)

Foundational Knowledge:

    GDPR Art. 5.2 (Accountability): The PA must demonstrate compliance. Logs are the primary evidence.

    Provvedimento Garante Privacy (Log Management): Guidelines on the retention period of system logs (normally not exceeding 6-24 months for administrative logs, longer only for specific security incident investigations).

    CAD (Codice dell'Amministrazione Digitale): Legal value of electronic documents and timestamps.

Tools and Practical Competencies:

    SIEM Configuration: Deploying Wazuh (Open Source) or Splunk to collect logs from Domain Controllers, Firewall di Sede Centrale, and Sistemi di Protocollo Informatico.

    Sysmon / Auditd: Configuration of specific logging for Process Creation and File Access to track who accessed the cartella_condivisa_delibere containing sensitive personnel data.

    Key Activities:

        Privileged Access Monitoring: Auditing all actions performed by members of the Domain Admins group. Logs must be tamper-proof and sent to a separate Log Collector not accessible to those same admins.

        GDPR Audit Readiness: Generating a report showing: *"On 2026-04-10 at 10:00, Employee X accessed Record Y (Codice Fiscale Z). Access was authorized based on the task of processing IMU rebates."*

        Forensic Timeline: In case of an investigation by the Corte dei Conti or Guardia di Finanza regarding a data leak, ability to reconstruct the exact sequence of events using Plaso/Timesketch.